---
// ProblemStatement.astro — "Why now" narrative between Hero and code showcase
---

<section class="section-pad problem-section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <span class="section-eyebrow" data-reveal>WHAT BREAKS FIRST</span>
    <h2 class="section-title problem-headline" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1">
      Long-running agents fail in boring, expensive ways.
    </h2>

    <div class="problem-grid">

      <div class="why-card" data-reveal="scale-up" data-reveal-delay="2">
        <div class="card-glow"></div>
        <div class="why-card-image">
          <img src="https://assets.kitaru.ai/content/site/34447ad2/k-prob-1-800.avif" srcset="https://assets.kitaru.ai/content/site/2cc2883d/k-prob-1-sm.avif 664w, https://assets.kitaru.ai/content/site/34447ad2/k-prob-1-800.avif 800w" alt="Agents die when your laptop sleeps" loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="400" height="225" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 33vw" onerror="this.style.display='none'" />
        </div>
        <div class="why-card-content">
          <h3>Hours of work disappear on routine failures</h3>
          <p>A laptop sleep, pod eviction, or API timeout can wipe a run that took hours to build. You burn tokens and start over.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="why-card" data-reveal="scale-up" data-reveal-delay="3">
        <div class="card-glow"></div>
        <div class="why-card-image">
          <img src="https://assets.kitaru.ai/content/site/80283a6e/k-prob-2-800.avif" srcset="https://assets.kitaru.ai/content/site/bfd1b9bd/k-prob-2-sm.avif 664w, https://assets.kitaru.ai/content/site/80283a6e/k-prob-2-800.avif 800w" alt="Agents can't coordinate" loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="400" height="225" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 33vw" onerror="this.style.display='none'" />
        </div>
        <div class="why-card-content">
          <h3>They need to wait on humans and other systems</h3>
          <p>Real agents pause for approvals, webhooks, and other agents. Fire-and-forget loops do not handle that well.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="why-card" data-reveal="scale-up" data-reveal-delay="4">
        <div class="card-glow"></div>
        <div class="why-card-image">
          <img src="https://assets.kitaru.ai/content/site/79a5c5af/k-prob-3-800.avif" srcset="https://assets.kitaru.ai/content/site/71979af8/k-prob-3-sm.avif 664w, https://assets.kitaru.ai/content/site/79a5c5af/k-prob-3-800.avif 800w" alt="Results vanish when agents crash" loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="400" height="225" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 33vw" onerror="this.style.display='none'" />
        </div>
        <div class="why-card-content">
          <h3>State either vanishes or gets stitched together by hand</h3>
          <p>Without checkpoints, artifacts, and memory, you lose context when things go wrong and debugging becomes guesswork.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <p class="problem-conclusion" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="5">
      That is why Kitaru focuses on runtime primitives: checkpoints, replay, wait/resume, and durable state on real infrastructure.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .problem-section {
    background: var(--color-bg);
  }

  .problem-headline {
    max-width: 700px;
  }

  .problem-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 20px;
    margin-top: 48px;
  }

  .problem-conclusion {
    margin-top: 40px;
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.8vw, 1.15rem);
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .problem-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  import { setupCardGlow } from '../scripts/card-glow';
  setupCardGlow('.problem-section .why-card');
</script>
